  <!-- Section 3.3: Sampling from a small population -->
  <section xml:id="sec-sampling-small-population">
    <title>Sampling from a small population</title>

    <introduction>
      <p>
        When we sample observations from a population, usually we're only sampling 
        a small fraction of the possible individuals or cases. However, sometimes 
        our sample size is large enough or the population is small enough that we 
        sample more than 10% of a population without replacement.
      </p>
    </introduction>

